.TH "hl_fw_load_fw_to_device" 9 "hl_fw_load_fw_to_device" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
hl_fw_load_fw_to_device \- Load F/W code to device's memory.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" hl_fw_load_fw_to_device
.BI "(struct hl_device *hdev "  ","
.BI "const char *fw_name "  ","
.BI "void __iomem *dst "  ","
.BI "u32 src_offset "  ","
.BI "u32 size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hdev" 12
pointer to hl_device structure.
.IP "fw_name" 12
the firmware image name
.IP "dst" 12
IO memory mapped address space to copy firmware to
.IP "src_offset" 12
offset in src FW to copy from
.IP "size" 12
amount of bytes to copy (0 to copy the whole binary)
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Copy fw code from firmware file to device memory.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, non-zero for failure.
